Now I see a potential issue! Look at line 14257-14261:

```cpp
if( dropoff_coords.empty() ) {
    you.add_msg_if_player( m_info,
                           _( "You have items to sort.  However, there are no valid locations to sort to." ) );
    stage = LAST;
    return;
}
```

When `dropoff_coords` is empty (all destinations unreachable), it sets `stage = LAST` and returns. In the next `do_turn`, since `stage == LAST` (not `DO` or `THINK` or `INIT`), it falls through to line 13414 `act.set_to_null()`.

But wait — `LAST` is a stage. Let me check what happens when `stage == LAST`:

```cpp
void zone_activity_actor::do_turn( player_activity &act, Character &you )
{
    update_vehicle_zone_cache();

    if( stage == UNINIT ) { stage = INIT; }
    if( stage == INIT ) { stage_init( act, you ); }
    if( stage == THINK ) { ... }
    if( stage == DO ) { ... }

    // If we got here without restarting the activity, it means we're done
    add_msg( m_info, _( "%s sorted out every item possible." ), ... );
    act.set_to_null();
}
```

So when `stage == LAST`, it falls through all the conditional blocks and sets `act.set_to_null()`. Then in derived `do_turn`, `act.is_null()` is true, `!you.has_destination()` is true, `had_viewport` is true → viewport is restored.

Hmm, this still seems like it should work. Let me now try the actual test scenario to see if there's a real issue or if I'm overthinking this.

Actually wait — let me look at line 14260 more carefully: `stage = LAST; return;`

This exits `stage_do`. Back in `zone_activity_actor::do_turn`:
```
if( stage == DO ) {
    stage_do( act, you );
