Line 285-287:
```cpp
if( actor ) {
    const activity_id prior_act_id = id();
    actor->do_turn( *this, you );
    ...
```

So `player_activity::do_turn` calls `actor->do_turn(*this, you)`. This passes `*this` (the `player_activity` object) as the `player_activity &act` parameter. When the base `zone_activity_actor::do_turn` calls `act.set_to_null()`, it nulls the same `player_activity` object that was passed.

Then line 290: `if( *this && prior_act_id != id() )` — checks if the activity is still valid and the id changed. After `set_to_null()`, `*this` is false (since `type.is_null()` returns true). So the function would continue executing.

